{{Otheruses4|the defunct sex theme park in Chongqing, China|the similar park in South Korea|Love Land (Korea)}}
'''Love Land''' was a [[sex]] [[theme park]] under construction in [[Chongqing]], [[China]]. The park was to include displays of giant [[genitalia]] and naked bodies, and host an exhibition on the history of sex along with sex technique workshops.<ref name="BBC">{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/world/asia-pacific/8053596.stm|title=China builds first sex theme park|date=May 16, 2009|publisher=BBC|accessdate=2009-05-17}}</ref> It was originally due to be opened in October 2009, but was demolished in May 2009, as it was deemed to be a negative influence on Chinese society.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.channelnewsasia.com/stories/lifestylenews/view/430040/1/.html|title=China builds first sex theme park|date=May 18, 2009|publisher=ChannelNewsAsia|accessdate=2009-05-18}}</ref><ref>http://www.foxnews.com/story/0,2933,520501,00.html</ref><ref name="NYT">{{cite news|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2009/05/19/world/asia/19china.html?_r=1&ref=global-home|title=Chinese City Is Chilly to a Sex Theme Park |last=Wong|first=Edward|date=2009-05-18|work=New York Times|accessdate=2009-05-19}}</ref>

